<section>
	<h2 id="icons">Icons</h2>
	<p>
		System icons are displayed at 24px, but are also available in varying sizes such as 18px and 12px.
		The content of an icon should remain inside the square container and when implementing,
		adequate space around the icon should be added to allow for legibility and touch.
		You may have icons with different sizes, but do not place any part of the icon outside of the live area.
	</p>
	<p>
		Asset names for icons are defined by the pattern <code><strong>wds-icons-ICON_NAME</strong></code>,
		e.g. <code>wds-icons-alert</code>.
	</p>
	<p>
		To apply default styles for an icon add <code class="format-code">.wds-icon</code> class to the <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> element.
		This class includes <code>fill: currentColor;</code> rule which means that the fill color is inherited from the parent.
		To change the icon's color you can either set <code>fill</code> on the <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> element or
		<code>color</code> on its parent. If the parent changes its color (e.g. on the hover state) it's propagated to the icon.
	</p>
</section>

